  "soap_summary": "Subjective: Patient (female) with 2 days of localized burning lower abdominal pain (just below umbilicus), gradually worsening and becoming constant. Reports mild nausea, feeling hot/sweaty, recent pink discoloration of urine, and increased urinary frequency. No dysuria, no vomiting, no diarrhea, no cough or shortness of breath. Past constipation last week that has improved. On etonogestrel (Implanon) implant. Assessment/Plan: Differential includes urinary tract infection, GI causes, and possible pregnancy. Plan to perform pregnancy test and other initial tests; clinician will arrange tests today. Empiric antibiotic prescribed (start today: one tablet twice daily for 3 days). Recommend paracetamol for pain and increased fluids; return if symptoms worsen or do not improve.",
